law.text: An employer that willfully fails to comply with an income-withholding order issued in another state and received for enforcement is subject to the same penalties that may be imposed for noncompliance with an order issued by a tribunal of this state.
law.history: Amended 2015 Ky. Acts ch. 18, sec. 37, effective June 24, 2015. -- Created 1998 Ky. Acts ch. 101, sec. 12, effective March 23, 1998.
